definition.value: An alpha-D-galactoside having a 1D-myo-inositol substituent at the anomeric position.
A tetrahydroxyflavanone that is taxifolin in which the hydroxy group at position 3' is substituted by a methoxy group. It is a metabolite of taxifolin.
A hydroxyquinoline that is kynurenic acid in which the hydrogens at positions 7 and 8 are replaced by hydroxy groups.
